1752	### A12. Zero-Downtime Schema Migration Policy (HIGH — addresses ISSUE-17)
1753	
1754	**Problem**: P1C adds indexes, P7C does backfills, A6 does partitioning — no protocol for doing this safely at 2000 users.
1755	
1756	**Expand/Contract Pattern**:
1757	```
1758	Phase 1 (Expand): Add new column/index/table — backward-compatible code
1759	Phase 2 (Migrate): Backfill data, dual-write if needed
1760	Phase 3 (Contract): Remove old column/index/table — only after all code uses new schema
1761	```
1762	
1763	**Rules**:
1764	1. **Additive-only migrations first**: ADD COLUMN (nullable), CREATE INDEX → safe, non-blocking
1765	2. **Column renames**: NEVER rename directly. Add new → backfill → switch code → drop old (3 releases)
1766	3. **Index creation**: Use `ALGORITHM=INPLACE, LOCK=NONE` for MySQL 8 InnoDB (online DDL)
1767	   ```php
1768	   DB::statement('CREATE INDEX idx_name ON table_name (col1, col2) ALGORITHM=INPLACE LOCK=NONE');
1769	   ```
1770	4. **Backfill large tables** (>1M rows): Use `chunkById(500)` during low-traffic window
1771	5. **Partitioning** (A6): Test on replica first, apply to primary during maintenance window
1772	6. **NEVER** drop columns or tables in same release as code change
1773	
1774	**Migration Pre-Flight Checklist**:
1775	- [ ] Migration is additive only (no DROP, RENAME, ALTER TYPE)
1776	- [ ] Tested on staging with production-volume data
1777	- [ ] `--pretend` output reviewed
1778	- [ ] Rollback migration exists and tested
1779	- [ ] Estimated lock time documented
