1860	### A14. Cache Stampede Prevention (HIGH — addresses ISSUE-21)
1861	
1862	**Problem**: P3 uses fixed short TTLs + broad entity-tag flush → synchronized expiry at 2000 users → DB spike.
1863	
1864	**Solution — 3 techniques in CacheService**:
1865	
1866	**1. TTL Jitter** (±20% randomization):
1867	```php
1868	// In CacheService::remember()
1869	$jitteredTtl = $ttl + random_int((int)(-$ttl * 0.2), (int)($ttl * 0.2));
1870	```
1871	
1872	**2. Single-Flight Locking** (prevent stampede):
1873	```php
1874	public function remember(array $tags, string $key, int $ttl, Closure $callback): mixed
1875	{
1876	    // ... existing CacheService logic ...
1877	    $lock = Cache::lock("lock:{$key}", 10); // 10s max wait
1878	    if ($lock->get()) {
1879	        try {
1880	            $value = $callback();
1881	            // store in cache...
1882	            return $value;
1883	        } finally {
1884	            $lock->release();
1885	        }
1886	    }
1887	    // Lock not acquired: return stale value or wait
1888	    return Cache::get($prefixedKey) ?? $callback();
1889	}
1890	```
1891	
1892	**3. Background Refresh for Dashboard Caches** (L3):
1893	```php
1894	// Schedule in app/Console/Kernel.php — refresh hot caches proactively
1895	$schedule->call(function () {
1896	    // Pre-warm dashboard caches every 4 minutes (before 5-min TTL expires)
1897	    app(FeeCollectionDashboardService::class)->getDashboard(/* current period */);
1898	    app(LeadershipDashboardService::class)->getDashboard();
1899	})->everyFourMinutes();
1900	```
1901	
1902	**4. Narrower Invalidation** — Instead of flushing entire `'invoices'` tag on any save:
1903	```php
1904	// Only flush list cache segments that include the affected entity
1905	$this->cacheService->flushTags(['invoices:customer:' . $invoice->customer_id]);
1906	$this->cacheService->flushTags(['invoices:status:' . $invoice->status]);
1907	// Keep unrelated segments warm
1908	```
