1962	### A16. Auth Hardening — CSRF, Session, Brute-Force (HIGH — addresses ISSUE-25, ISSUE-26)
1963	
1964	**Problem**: Multi-node deployment + 2000 users needs explicit CSRF recovery, session security, and abuse protection.
1965	
1966	**1. CSRF Bootstrap/Recovery**:
1967	```php
1968	// Sanctum CSRF cookie — ensure frontend calls this before first POST
1969	Route::get('/sanctum/csrf-cookie', ...); // Already exists via Sanctum
1970	
1971	// Frontend: auto-retry on 419
1972	// In apiFetch.ts:
1973	if (response.status === 419) {
1974	    await fetch('/sanctum/csrf-cookie', { credentials: 'include' });
1975	    return apiFetch(url, options); // retry once
1976	}
1977	```
1978	
1979	**2. Session Security**:
1980	```php
1981	// config/session.php — hardened
1982	'same_site' => 'lax',           // Prevent CSRF via cross-site requests
1983	'secure' => true,                // HTTPS only
1984	'http_only' => true,             // No JS access to session cookie
1985	'expire_on_close' => false,
1986	```
1987	
1988	**3. Session Regeneration**:
1989	```php
1990	// On login (already done by Sanctum, verify)
1991	$request->session()->regenerate();
1992	
1993	// On privilege elevation (e.g., password change, role change)
1994	$request->session()->regenerate(true); // destroy old session
1995	```
1996	
1997	**4. Progressive Brute-Force Protection**:
1998	```php
1999	// AppServiceProvider.php — enhanced login throttle
2000	RateLimiter::for('auth.login', function (Request $request) {
2001	    $key = Str::lower($request->input('username')) . '|' . $request->ip();
2002	    return [
2003	        Limit::perMinute(5)->by($key),                    // 5 attempts/min per user+IP
2004	        Limit::perMinute(30)->by($request->ip()),         // 30 attempts/min per IP (cross-user)
2005	        Limit::perHour(100)->by($request->ip()),          // 100 attempts/hour per IP
2006	    ];
2007	});
2008	
2009	// Password change — tighter limit
2010	RateLimiter::for('auth.password', function (Request $request) {
2011	    return Limit::perMinute(3)->by($request->user()?->id);
2012	});
2013	```
2014	
2015	**5. Trusted Proxies** (for load balancer):
2016	```php
2017	// app/Http/Middleware/TrustProxies.php
2018	protected $proxies = '*'; // Or specific LB IPs
2019	protected $headers = Request::HEADER_X_FORWARDED_FOR |
2020	                     Request::HEADER_X_FORWARDED_HOST |
2021	                     Request::HEADER_X_FORWARDED_PORT |
2022	                     Request::HEADER_X_FORWARDED_PROTO;
2023	```
